Don't ever use your credit card at this establishment. They will act as if you didn't hand them your card two minutes ago to run it and then it mysteriously appears after you leave with double charges on your account. The card was no where, we all looked and I know I handed him my card! The owner whom promised he would do right by me, STILL a month later hasn't contacted me back. I spoke with him in person to try and rectify the situation but got no where.  As a business owner you should take care of your customers complaints immediately. Not brush them off. My credit card being "missing" I had to cancel right before the holidays causing all kinds of problems. From not being able to get cash as it was the weekend,  calling bill companies to stop payment, and the list goes on! Offering me a drink, which i did not want, isn't going to cut it. Again , he promised he would make right a VERY awful situation. My friends and I would go in monthly for dinner and drinks and spend a good amount of money. You have lost not only 20 plus as paying customers but all respect as a person and business owner especially within our small Kenmore community!! And no I STILL have not gotten my money back from him!!!

Took a buddy for his birthday that lives in the neighborhood and I was really impressed.  The highlight of the meal was an apple and walnut salad.  I ordered the appetizer size and it was perfect size to start my meal.  The spinach and artichoke dip was average but pretty much what was expected.  For entree I tried the Hot Pepper Pasta which was also very delicious.  The size was perfect although must in WNY would have expected it larger.  But let's remember you would pay for food you did not need.  The size was great for the $12.  Cranberry Mule was delicious too.  Service also a high point, the server even overheard that it was my buddies birthday and bought one of his beers for him.

Worst experience ive ever had in any type of establishment ever. Nobody answered the phone, walked in to place a to go order as the food is pretty good. The bartender informed me they do not accept to go orders and they do not answer the phone, i attempted to engage the bartender in conversation about the to go orders, he informed me they do not want, or need customers like me. After informing him that to go business is better than no business and i simply dont understand that decision he then told me that he doesnt f'n know and he doesnt f'n care and asked me why i was even talking to him. I have never and will never experience such disrespect at a restaurant. If you want to eat at a place that treats you like your lucky to be eating there instead of the other way around then this is the place for you. The only time i will ever visit this place again is to have a drink out in front of it when they close there doors and go out of business, which im sure wont be long if they continue to treat people with such disrespect and arrogance.
